quran[32]{c,v,t,f}:
  86,1,"By the sky and the night comer –",""
  86,2,"and how do you know what the night comer is?",""
  86,3,"It is the star of piercing brightness<sup>1</sup> –","[1] Whose light pierces through the darkness or through the sky."
  86,4,"there is no soul except that there is a watcher over it.",""
  86,5,"Let man reflect on what he was created from.",""
  86,6,"He was created from a spurting fluid,",""
  86,7,"emerging from between the backbone and the ribs<sup>2</sup>.","[2] Both testes and ovaries are sustained by arteries originating between the backbone and the ribcage."
  86,8,"Indeed, Allah is able to bring him back to life.",""
  86,9,"On the Day when all secrets will be disclosed<sup>3</sup>,","[3] The secrets will be examined, disclosing the real intentions and faiths people harbored, distinguishing between righteous and evil therefrom."
  86,10,"he will then have no power, nor any helper.",""
  86,11,"By the sky and its recurring rain<sup>4</sup>,","[4] And sun, moon, stars, clouds, heat, etc."
  86,12,"and by the earth that cracks open [with the sprout of plants],",""
  86,13,"Indeed, this [Qur’an] is a decisive word,",""
  86,14,"which is not for amusement.",""
  86,15,"Indeed, they are devising a plan.",""
  86,16,"I am too devising a plan.",""
  86,17,"So bear with the disbelievers, and give them respite for a while<sup>5</sup>.","[5] i.e., Do not be in haste in seeking their punishment and destruction."
  87,1,"Glorify the name of your Lord, the Most High,",""
  87,2,"Who created and fashioned in due proportion,",""
  87,3,"and Who determined [the creation] then inspired them,",""
  87,4,"and Who brings forth the pasture,",""
  87,5,"then makes it into withered chaff.",""
  87,6,"We will teach you [the Qur’an], so you will not forget,",""
  87,7,"except what Allah wills<sup>1</sup>, for indeed He knows what is manifest and what is hidden.","[1] i.e., except what Allah wills to make you forget for wisdom such as abrogating or replacing a ruling by another."
  87,8,"We will guide you to the easy way<sup>2</sup>.","[2] To the way of Islam which brings about ease in this life and attainment of Paradise in the Hereafter, or will give you opportunities for righteous deeds that lead to Paradise."
  87,9,"So remind, if the reminder should benefit<sup>3</sup>.","[3] Wherever this Qur’an will be heard."
  87,10,"He who fears Allah will take heed,",""
  87,11,"but the wretched will avoid it,",""
  87,12,"who will enter the Great Fire,",""
  87,13,"wherein he will neither die nor live.",""
  87,14,"Indeed, he who purifies himself will attain success,",""
  87,15,"and remembers his Lord’s Name and prays.",""
